When off-line objective functions are considered, the kinematic behavior of the semi-trailing arm is simulated. In this case, it is assumed that the vehicle is in the rest; however, merely the body rolls. It is obvious that in off-line process, the vehicle dynamics and tire–road interaction do not enter to the simulation process. By the off-line objective function, variations of the geometric dimensions due to the roll of the vehicle body are investigated. These variations affect the dynamic behavior of the vehicle. For the rolls to enhance the handling and stability, the following conditions are required:
variation of the camber should be maximized f1 (enhancement of handling);
variation of the toe angle should be minimized f2 (enhancement of handling);
variation of the track must be maximized f3 (enhancement of stability). then, the off-line objective functions are introduced as follows (24) where γL is the camber angle of the outer wheels with respect to the rotation direction of the roll angle of body.

An excessive body sideslip angle of a vehicle makes the vehicle’s yaw motion insensitive to the driver’s steering input and threatens the lateral stability of a vehicle. Thus, the body sideslip angle should be maintained as small as possible to assure the lateral stability.19–21 So the on-line1 objective functions will be defined such that in each time of motion:


error of the actual yaw rate to its desired value should be minimized, g1;

lateral sideslip of the body should be minimized, g2.

In addition to kinematic criteria such as ψ·d and β, the handling and stability performances of a vehicle can be explained based on the kinetic criteria such as normal forces from road on the wheels during the motion. According to the latter criteria, the on-line2 objective functions are defined such that in each time of motion:


for better handling, the difference of normal forces on the wheels of each axle should be minimized, h1;

more stability and road holding require that the difference of normal force on the opposite wheels of each front and rear axles should be minimized, h2.
